Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Place @white bread{2} in a #large bowl{} with @milk{1/3%cup}. Break up with your hands until pasty. Add @ground beef{20%oz}, @meatloaf spice blend{2%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of @pepper{pinch}. Mix with hands until just combined. Shape mixture into four 1-inch-thick loaves.

Place meatloaves on a #baking sheet{}. Brush a layer of @ketchup{2%tbsp} onto each. Bake in oven until no longer pink in center, about ~{25%minutes}.

Cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{32%oz} into ¾-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with a large pinch of @salt{} and enough @water{} to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain and return to pot.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely chop @chives{1/4%oz}(finely chopped). Toss @green beans{12%oz}, a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} on another baking sheet. Roast in oven until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add shallot and cook, tossing, until softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{2} and @water{3/4%cup} and bring to a simmer. Let bubble until slightly thickened and saucy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @pepper{}.

Meanwhile, add half the chives, @milk{2/3%cup}, and @butter{2%tbsp} to pot with potatoes. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Divide between plates, then top with green beans and a meatloaf. Drizzle with gravy and garnish with remaining chives.